ciscoCallHistoryMib.name: ciscoCallHistoryMib

revisions.description: Fix typo which caused conflicting syntax.
Add a new object ciscoCallHistoryDialReason to the call history table.
Add new objects to the call history table to store the time of day, and transmitted/received packets/bytes.
Add new objects to the call history table to store the advice of charge information for recorded units or currency type, amount and multipler.

ciscoCallHistoryMib.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wan@cisco.com
ciscoCallHistoryMib.description: The MIB module to describe and store the call information of the routers for accounting purposes.

ciscoCallHistoryTableMaxLength.name: ciscoCallHistoryTableMaxLength
ciscoCallHistoryTableMaxLength.description: The upper limit on the number of entries that the ciscoCallHistoryTable may contain. A value of 0 will prevent any history from being retained. When this table is full, the oldest entry will be deleted and the new one will be created.

ciscoCallHistoryRetainTimer.name: ciscoCallHistoryRetainTimer
ciscoCallHistoryRetainTimer.description: The minimum amount of time that an ciscoCallHistoryEntry will be maintained before being deleted. A value of 0 will prevent any history from being retained, but will not prevent callCompletion traps being genarated.

ciscoCallHistoryTable.name: ciscoCallHistoryTable
ciscoCallHistoryTable.description: A table containing information about specific calls to a specific destination.

ciscoCallHistoryEntry.name: ciscoCallHistoryEntry
ciscoCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a single Connection.

ciscoCallHistoryStartTime.name: ciscoCallHistoryStartTime
ciscoCallHistoryStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this call history entry was created. This will be useful for an NMS to retrieve all calls after a specific time.

ciscoCallHistoryIndex.name: ciscoCallHistoryIndex
ciscoCallHistoryIndex.description: Index variable to access the CallHistoryEntry objects of the ciscoCallHistoryTable.

ciscoCallHistoryCallingNumber.name: ciscoCallHistoryCallingNumber
ciscoCallHistoryCallingNumber.description: The calling number for this call. If the number is not available, then it will have a length of zero. The variable is instantiated if this is an incoming call.

ciscoCallHistoryCalledNumber.name: ciscoCallHistoryCalledNumber
ciscoCallHistoryCalledNumber.description: The number this call is connected to. This variable is instantiated if this is an outgoing call.

ciscoCallHistoryInterfaceNumber.name: ciscoCallHistoryInterfaceNumber
ciscoCallHistoryInterfaceNumber.description: This is the ifIndex value of the highest number of interface through which the call was made.

ciscoCallHistoryDestinationAddress.name: ciscoCallHistoryDestinationAddress
ciscoCallHistoryDestinationAddress.description: The address of the host this call is connected to, if it is available. Most devices/routers connected to an interface have an address and this object will store that. The variable is not instantiated if it is not available.

ciscoCallHistoryDestinationHostName.name: ciscoCallHistoryDestinationHostName
ciscoCallHistoryDestinationHostName.description: The name of the host this call is connected to. Most devices/routers connected to an interface have a name and this object will store that name.

ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectCause.name: ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectCause
ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectCause.description: The reason for the call termination.

ciscoCallHistoryCallConnectionTime.name: ciscoCallHistoryCallConnectionTime
ciscoCallHistoryCallConnectionTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was connected.

ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectTime.name: ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectTime
ciscoCallHistoryCallDisconnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call got disconnected last.

ciscoCallHistoryDialReason.name: ciscoCallHistoryDialReason
ciscoCallHistoryDialReason.description: The reason for initiating this call. This may include the destination address of the interesting packet that forced us to dial. This variable is instantiated for an outgoing call.

ciscoCallHistoryConnectTimeOfDay.name: ciscoCallHistoryConnectTimeOfDay
ciscoCallHistoryConnectTimeOfDay.description: The time of day at the time of call connect.

ciscoCallHistoryDisconnectTimeOfDay.name: ciscoCallHistoryDisconnectTimeOfDay
ciscoCallHistoryDisconnectTimeOfDay.description: The time of day when the call disconnected.

ciscoCallHistoryTransmitPackets.name: ciscoCallHistoryTransmitPackets
ciscoCallHistoryTransmitPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryTransmitBytes.name: ciscoCallHistoryTransmitBytes
ciscoCallHistoryTransmitBytes.description: Number of Bytes transmitted when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryReceivePackets.name: ciscoCallHistoryReceivePackets
ciscoCallHistoryReceivePackets.description: Number of packets received when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryReceiveBytes.name: ciscoCallHistoryReceiveBytes
ciscoCallHistoryReceiveBytes.description: Number of Bytes received when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryRecordedUnits.name: ciscoCallHistoryRecordedUnits
ciscoCallHistoryRecordedUnits.reference: ISDN AOC supplementary service DSS1 protocol ETS 300 182
ciscoCallHistoryRecordedUnits.description: Advice of Charge recorded units when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryCurrency.name: ciscoCallHistoryCurrency
ciscoCallHistoryCurrency.reference: ISDN AOC supplementary service DSS1 protocol ETS 300 182

ciscoCallHistoryCurrencyAmount.name: ciscoCallHistoryCurrencyAmount
ciscoCallHistoryCurrencyAmount.reference: ISDN AOC supplementary service DSS1 protocol ETS 300 182
ciscoCallHistoryCurrencyAmount.description: Advice of Charge currency amount when this call was up.

ciscoCallHistoryMultiplier.name: ciscoCallHistoryMultiplier
ciscoCallHistoryMultiplier.reference: ISDN AOC supplementary service DSS1 protocol ETS 300 182
ciscoCallHistoryMultiplier.description: Advice of Charge multiplier for currency amount
